Description: Modern Linux screen recorder and GIF/video editor
 GIF Forge records a region, window or screen on Wayland or X11, then lets you
 refine the result on a timeline (trim, cut, reorder, retime, crop, undo/redo)
 before exporting an optimized GIF, WebM or APNG. Projects are saveable and
 survive crashes.
 .
 It is built in Python with GTK4 and Libadwaita and uses ffmpeg (and optionally
 gifski) for encoding. Wayland capture goes through the ScreenCast portal and
 PipeWire; X11 capture uses ffmpeg's xcbgrab.
